    {
      "instruction": "<p>Trim your <strong>green beans</strong>, then chop them into bite-sized pieces and add them to the dish with the <strong>chopped tomato</strong>,<strong> crushed garlic </strong>and<strong> chopped ginger</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>brown rice</strong>, <strong>tamari soy sauce </strong>and 650ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[850ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1.1L] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>with a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, stir in your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>with your<strong> creamed coconut </strong>until the creamed coconut has dissolved</p>",
